"n. 猛攻，猛袭 【英】 n. 猛攻，猛袭(a fierce attack) 【记】 on+slaught(打击)→ 猛打，猛攻; 【同】 参考：slaughter(屠 宰) 【例】 a coordinated onslaught on enemy airfields 无 无 onslaught (n.)  1620s, anslaight, somehow from or on analogy of Dutch aanslag ""attack,"" from Middle Dutch aenslach, from aen ""on"" (see on) + slach ""blow,"" related to slaen ""slay."" Spelling influenced by obsolete (since c.1400) English slaught (n.) ""slaughter,"" from Old English sleaht (see slaughter (n.)). No record of its use in 18c.; apparently revived by Scott."
